oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Performance - Hank Williams III - 2009-10-10
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance by Hank Williams III at the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on October 10, 2009. In support of a Hank Williams: Family Tradition exhibit. Includes interview segment by Michael McCall
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Hank Williams III
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Performances include; Straight To Hell; Thrown Out Of The Bar; Smoke And Wine; Country Heroes; Seven Months, 39 days; Pills I Took; Six Pack Of Beer; D Ray White; P.F.F.; I'll Never Get Out Of This World Alive; Fiddle instrumental which includes Boil The Cabbage Down; Mississippi Mud; Going Back To Texas; Trashville; Not Everybody Likes Us; Dick In Dixie; Life Of Sin; Hellbilly; unidentified; interview;
